<h1>Mapbox GL Style Reference</h1>

<p>The Mapbox GL style is an object that defines what data to draw, the order to draw it in, and how to style the data when drawing it. The JSON structure follows the renderer implementation very closely. It provides the basic building blocks out of which more complex styles can be built.</p>

<p class='space-bottom4 quiet small'>Key: 
  <span class='icon alert quiet micro space-right inline' title='Required'>required</span>
  <span class='icon levels quiet micro space-right inline' title='Supports function values'>supports function values</span>
  <span class='icon opacity quiet micro space-right inline' title='Transitionable'>transitionable</span>
</p>

